UID:pulpdeb@cfgmgmtcamp.eu
SUMMARY:Managing large Debian repositories with Pulp (and less than 50GiB of RAM)
ORGANIZER:Quirin Pamp
CATEGORIES:talk
DTSTAMP:20181231T000000Z
TZID:Europe-Brussels
DTSTART:20190204T170000
DTEND:20190204T172500
DESCRIPTION:"Pulp is a platform for software repository management.  The pulp_deb plugin adds Apt-repository support for Debian packages.  Until recently, the pulp_deb implementation did not scale well for large repositories.  Synchronizing a full Debian or Ubuntu release (typically containing around 50,000 Packages)would routinely take hours before falling victim to the OOM-killer.  This talk discusses the changes we employed to fix this lamentable state of affairs.  It concludes with lessons learned for the development of pulp_deb 3.  "
