UID:fromback@cfgmgmtcamp.eu
SUMMARY:Tool migration - from Puppet to mgmt and back
ORGANIZER:Felix Frank
CATEGORIES:talk
DTSTAMP:20181229T000000Z
TZID:Europe-Brussels
DTSTART:20190204T150000
DTEND:20190204T155500
DESCRIPTION:"Switching out the back bone of your automation tool chain is usually painful.  It likely involves rewriting all your infrastructure code,and will either require a scary over-night cut-off, or a period in which two tools run concurrently,with operators carefully shifting functionality one step at a time.  With mgmt's support for Puppet code, migrating becomes a lot more natural.  This session does a deep dive and shows how mgmt will allow you to use and maintain a mixed code base of both Puppet's and mgmt's DSLs.  "
