UID:4thgenauto@cfgmgmtcamp.eu
SUMMARY:Fourth Generation Automation: Uniting Models and Tasks
ORGANIZER:Eric Sorenson
CATEGORIES:keynote
DTSTAMP:20181226T000000Z
TZID:Europe-Brussels
DTSTART:20190204T120000
DTEND:20190204T124000
DESCRIPTION:"To borrow a phrase, "In the beginning was the command line." Then we had ISConf and CFEngine, and things were good... for a while.  Puppet and Chef came along, embodying the idea that infrastructure code should behave like application code.  More recently, Ansible brought the concept of idempotent resources to imperative workflows, but stops short of modelling in favor of radical simplicity.  Now we're wondering: is it possible to get the best of both worlds?  Can we get model-based guarantees plus orchestrated action?  I think the answer is "yes" and in this talk I will explore an emerging "fourth generation" of config management tools that attempt to bring the beneficial properties of models together with orchestrated action. In full disclosure, I'll talk about Puppet's Bolt and Lyra projects, but the talk will not be vendor-specific as tools like Terraform and OpsMop also exemplify this approach."
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:@"<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC ""-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN""><HTML><BODY><p>To borrow a phrase, &ldquo;In the beginning was the command line.&rdquo; Then we had ISConf and CFEngine, and things were good&hellip; for a while.</p><p>Puppet and Chef came along, embodying the idea that infrastructure code should behave like application code.  Morerecently, Ansible brought the concept of idempotent resources to imperative workflows, but stops short of modelling infavor of radical simplicity.</p><p>Now we&rsquo;re wondering: is it possible to get the best of both worlds?<br />Can we get model-based guarantees plus orchestrated action?</p><p>I think the answer is &ldquo;yes&rdquo; and in this talk I will explore an emerging &ldquo;fourth generation&rdquo; of config management toolsthat attempt to bring the beneficial properties of models together with orchestrated action. In full disclosure, I&rsquo;lltalk about Puppet&rsquo;s Bolt and Lyra projects, but the talk will not be vendor-specific as tools like Terraform and OpsMopalso exemplify this approach.</p></BODY></HTML>";
URL:https://cfgmgmtcamp.eu/schedule/monday/4thgenauto/
LOCATION:D.AUD
